<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - REMOVE - AUXILIARY SECTION WITH TAPERED BEARINGS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="8">
        <title>AUXILIARY SECTION WITH TAPERED BEARINGS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>There can be different bolt lengths; note their location.</para>
            <para>Auxiliary sections can be removed either with the transmission in the horizontal position or the
                vertical position.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>To remove the auxiliary section in the horizontal position.</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the four (4) bolts and the auxiliary countershaft rear bearing cover, gasket, and
                    rear bearing shim (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301727">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301727" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301727" filename="../figg13/G1301727.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 27. Remove Auxiliary Countershaft Bearing Cover</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install auxiliary countershaft retaining straps with 2-3/8" NC x 1" and 1-3/8" NC x
                    2-1/2" clean bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301728">Figure 28</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301728" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301728" filename="../figg13/G1301728.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 28. Install Countershaft Retaining Straps</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Do not use an air gun. Tighten by hand until the bolts are snug.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolts that attach the auxiliary section to the front section (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301729">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301729" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301729" filename="../figg13/G1301729.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 29. Insert Bolts in Housing Flange</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the two (2) longest bolts in the housing flange tapped holes (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301729">Figure 29</hotlnk>). Tighten evenly to move the auxiliary section away
                    from the front box. Go far enough to break the gasket seal.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolts from the tapped holes.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach an auxiliary section hanger bracket to the top of the auxiliary section (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301730">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301730" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301730" filename="../figg13/G1301730.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 30. Attach Hanger Bracket</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach a lifting chain to the auxiliary section hanger bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301730">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Move assembly to the rear until auxiliary section is free.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the gasket and clean all mounting surfaces of gasket material.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>To Remove The Auxiliary Section In The Vertical Position.</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With blocks under the clutch housing to prevent input shaft damage, place transmission
                    in the vertical position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the four (4) bolts and the auxiliary countershaft rear bearing cover, gasket, and
                    rear bearing shim (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301731">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301731" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301731" filename="../figg13/G1301731.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 31. Auxiliary Countershaft Rear Bearing Cover</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install auxiliary countershaft retaining straps with 2-3/8" NC x 1" and 1-3/8" NC x
                    2-1/2" bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301732">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301732" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301732" filename="../figg13/G1301732.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 32. Retaining Straps</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolts that attach the auxiliary box to the front section (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301733">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301733" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301733" filename="../figg13/G1301733.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 33. Auxiliary Box</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a steel bar through the yoke (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301734">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301734" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301734" filename="../figg13/G1301734.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 34. Bar Through Yoke</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach a lifting chain to the steel bar (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301734">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift assembly from the front section.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the gasket and clean all mounting surfaces of gasket material.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
